The first phase of the Webuye Pan Paper Mills will be opened on December 15, President Uhuru Kenyatta has said.He said more than 500 people will be employed as the mill is revived. I was to come here in December to open the first phase of the mill that has been completed, but since I was around here I thought it wise that I should come and see for myself where the process has reached, the President said.He addressed residents after touring the factory on Thursday. This was after he attended the first graduation ceremony at Kibabii University College.The President said he is happy with the job being done by the investor. We have agreed with the Rai family that by June next year they will have doubled the capacity and the number of people employed here, he said. Uhuru said he is committed to see all the factories that are stalled in Western and across the country revived to create jobs. He said there is no need for leaders engaging in retrogressive tribal politics that will not put food on the tables of wananchi .